  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Where can you keep updated on the latest technology news?",
  "response": "To stay updated on the latest technology news, you can follow various sources, including:\n\n1. **Technology News Websites**:\n   - **TechCrunch**: Offers news on startups and new internet products.\n   - **The Verge**: Covers the intersection of technology, science, art, and culture.\n   - **CNET**: Provides reviews, news, and advice on technology.\n   - **Engadget**: Offers news and reviews on gadgets and consumer electronics.\n\n2. **News Aggregators**:\n   - **Google News**: Customize your feed to show the latest in tech.\n   - **Feedly**: Aggregate your favorite technology blogs and news sources in one place.\n\n3. **Social Media Platforms**:\n   - **Twitter**: Follow tech journalists and industry leaders for real-time updates.\n   - **LinkedIn**: Join technology groups and follow companies for news and insights.\n\n4. **Podcasts**:\n   - **Reply All**: Focuses on stories about how people shape the internet.\n   - **The Vergecast**: A weekly roundup of tech news and discussions.\n\n5. **YouTube Channels**:\n   - Channels like **Marques Brownlee**, **Linus Tech Tips**, and **Unbox Therapy** often cover the latest tech trends and products.\n\n6. **Newsletters**:\n   - Subscribe to newsletters from sources like **The Hustle**, **Morning Brew**, or specific technology publications that offer regular updates.\n\n7. **RSS Feeds**:\n   - Use an RSS reader to subscribe to feeds from your favorite tech blogs and news sites.\n\n8. **Online Forums and Communities**:\n   - **Reddit**: Subreddits like r/technology, r/technews, and r/gadgets provide community-driven news and discussions.\n\nBy combining these sources, you can stay well-informed about the latest developments in technology.",
